    <section class="body-content">
        <section class="uni-box layout-1 section-shadow">
            <div class="main-section cf">
                <div class="padding_40 cf t_s-13 t_c-gray article-content article-text jsTextSize" data-font-size="13">
                    <h5>The Minister of Science and Higher Education (PL: MNiSW) has awarded scholarships to 402 students for outstanding achievements in academia, the arts or sport. Among the recipients are 31 students representing the University of Warsaw.</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Out of 1,155 applications meeting the criteria, the Minister of Science and Higher Education awarded 402 scholarships across 48 disciplines for significant academic, artistic or sporting achievements. The scholarship is a one-off payment of 17,000 PLN.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="ramka">
<h5>Scholarship recipients from the UW:</h5>
<p>• Melike Fatma Alsaç (linguistics)<br />
• Weronika Araszkiewicz (psychology)<br />
• Dawid Bugajewski (physical sciences)<br />
• Dawid Dąbrowski (physical sciences)<br />
• Amadeusz Dominik Dydniański (physical sciences)<br />
• Adam Józef Gonet (socio-economic geography and spatial planning)<br />
• Maksymilian Augustyn Grądz (law)<br />
• Liwia Jarocka (psychology student awarded for sporting achievements)<br />
• Katarzyna Maria Jarosińska (biotechnology)<br />
• Nikodem Włodzimierz Kaczprzak (law)<br />
• Jan Krzysztof Kossacki (physical sciences)<br />
• Dominika Kraska (literary studies)<br />
• Krzysztof Król (astronomy)<br />
• Adrianna Julia Kruk (physical sciences)<br />
• Artur Son Le Hoang (physical sciences)<br />
• Magdalena Otylia Marynowska (international relations)<br />
• Weronika Amelia Mazur (psychology)<br />
• Joanna Ewelina Mędrzycka (physical sciences)<br />
• Romuald Maria Milcarek (archaeology)<br />
• Filip Stefan Misiak (law)<br />
• Michał Mozyrski (archaeology)<br />
• Jan Oleksiuk (law)<br />
• Aniela Partyga (sociology)<br />
• Lena Solska (Polish studies)<br />
• Michał Rafał Stanowski (computer science)<br />
• Michał Jakub Szewczyk (sociology)<br />
• Wiktoria Stanisława Szymanek (biotechnology)<br />
• Maciej Szyszko (physical sciences)<br />
• Jakub Michał Witczak (international relations)<br />
• Maja Ida Wróblewska (sociology)<br />
• Oliwier Zając (geography)</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
                    <h2 style="line-height:30px;">23 lutego 2014 r. uruchomiony został nowy serwis internetowy Uniwersytetu Warszawskiego. <br />Informacje o uczelni znajdują się na nowej stronie głównej oraz w portalu informacyjnym UW. <br />Możesz skorzystać z pomocy wyszukiwarki.
                    </h2>
                    <h3 style="margin:20px 0;">Archiwalna strona dostępna jest pod adresem <a href="http://arch.uw.edu.pl">http://arch.uw.edu.pl</a></h3>
                                        
